\u0435\u0434\u043d\u0430\u0442\u0430 \u0437\u0430 \u0415\u0432\u0440\u043e\u043f\u0435\u0439\u0441\u043a\u0438\u044f \u0441\u044a\u044e\u0437 |url=https://dnes.dir.bg/obshtestvo/osigurenostta-s-bolnichni-legla-v-balgariya-e-nad-srednata-za-evropeyskiya-sayuz |accessdate=18 March 2020}}</ref> However, Chief Health Inspector Angel Kunchev stated on 5 March that there is a shortage of medical personnel.<ref>{{cite news |title=\u0410\u043d\u0433\u0435\u043b \u041a\u0443\u043d\u0447\u0435\u0432: \u0410\u043a\u043e \u0441\u0435 \u043f\u043e\u044f\u0432\u0438 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441 \u0443 \u043d\u0430\u0441, \u0449\u0435 \u0438\u043c\u0430\u043c\u0435 \u043f\u0440\u043e\u0431\u043b\u0435\u043c \u0441 \u043d\u0435\u0434\u043e\u0441\u0442\u0438\u0433\u0430 \u043d\u0430 \u043b\u0435\u043a\u0430\u0440\u0438 |url=https://btvnovinite.bg/predavania/tazi-sutrin/zashto-se-stigna-do-remont-na-remonta-pri-rektorata-i-graf-ignatiev.html |accessdate=18 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nFollowing the announcement of positive SARS-CoV-2 test results, the Bulgarian government immediately banned the exports of protective equipment and placed orders for masks and protective suits to local manufacturers. In addition, 30,000 masks and 50,000 protective suits will be delivered by Turkey.<ref>{{cite news |title=\u0424\u043e\u0440\u0441\u043c\u0430\u0436\u043e\u0440\u043d\u043e\u0442\u043e \u043f\u0440\u043e\u0438\u0437\u0432\u043e\u0434\u0441\u0442\u0432\u043e \u043d\u0430 \u0437\u0430\u0449\u0438\u0442\u043d\u0438 \u043e\u0431\u043b\u0435\u043a\u043b\u0430 \u0438 \u043c\u0430\u0441\u043a\u0438 \u0449\u0435 \u0435 \u0431\u0435\u0437 \u043f\u0435\u0447\u0430\u043b\u0431\u0430 |url=https://www.dnevnik.bg/bulgaria/2020/03/08/4038200_forsmajornoto_proizvodstvo_na_zashtitni_oblekla_i/ |accessdate=8 March 2020}}</ref> Some 111,000 suits and masks are required every month and the government plans to distribute them to health workers, social assistants, law enforcement personnel and border guards.<ref>{{cite news |title=\u0411\u044a\u043b\u0433\u0430\u0440\u0441\u043a\u0438 \u0444\u0438\u0440\u043c\u0438 \u0437\u0430\u043f\u043e\u0447\u0432\u0430\u0442 \u043f\u0440\u043e\u0438\u0437\u0432\u043e\u0434\u0441\u0442\u0432\u043e \u043d\u0430 \u0437\u0430\u0449\u0438\u0442\u043d\u0438 \u043e\u0431\u043b\u0435\u043a\u043b\u0430 \u0438 \u043c\u0430\u0441\u043a\u0438 |url=https://dnes.dir.bg/obshtestvo/balgarski-firmi-zapochvat-proizvodstvo-na-zashtitni-oblekla-i-maski |accessdate=8 March 2020}}</ref> [[Stolichna Municipality|Sofia Municipality]] has increased disinfections to four times daily at public institutions and in public transport.<ref>{{cite news |title=\u041c\u0435\u0440\u043a\u0438 \u0441\u0440\u0435\u0449\u0443 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441\u0430 \u0432 \u0421\u043e\u0444\u0438\u044f. \u0417\u0430\u043f\u043e\u0447\u0432\u0430\u0442 \u0434\u0435\u0437\u0438\u043d\u0444\u0435\u043a\u0446\u0438\u0438 4 \u043f\u044a\u0442\u0438 \u0434\u043d\u0435\u0432\u043d\u043e |url=https://dnes.dir.bg/sofia/merki-sreshtu-koronavirusa-v-sofiya-zapochvat-dezinfektsii-4-pati-dnevno |accessdate=8 March 2020}}</ref> Personnel in all hospitals is being screened for the disease.<ref>{{cite news |title=\u041d\u044f\u043c\u0430 \u043d\u043e\u0432\u0438 \u0437\u0430\u0440\u0430\u0437\u0435\u043d\u0438 \u0441 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441, \u0438\u0437\u0441\u043b\u0435\u0434\u0432\u0430\u0442 \u043d\u0430\u0434 140 \u043a\u043e\u043d\u0442\u0430\u043a\u0442\u043d\u0438|url=https://www.dnes.bg/obshtestvo/2020/03/08/niama-novi-zarazeni-s-koronavirus-izsledvat-nad-140-kontaktni.441430 |accessdate=8 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nBy mid-March, large-scale imports of protective equipment from Vietnam, China and India had begun. Many volunteers were also signing up to join the handling of the crisis, including [[Nikola Vaptsarov Naval Academy]] cadets.<ref>{{cite news |title=85 \u0445\u0438\u043b. \u043e\u0431\u043b\u0435\u043a\u043b\u0430 \u0438 15 \u0445\u0438\u043b. \u043c\u0430\u0441\u043a\u0438 \u043f\u0440\u0438\u0441\u0442\u0438\u0433\u0430\u0442 \u043e\u0442 \u0422\u0443\u0440\u0446\u0438\u044f, \u0432\u0430\u0440\u043d\u0435\u043d\u0441\u043a\u0438\u0442\u0435 \u043a\u0443\u0440\u0441\u0430\u043d\u0442\u0438 \u0433\u043e\u0442\u043e\u0432\u0438 \u0437\u0430 \u0434\u043e\u0431\u0440\u043e\u0432\u043e\u043b\u0446\u0438 |url=https://dariknews.bg/novini/bylgariia/85-hil.-oblekla-i-15-hil.-maski-pristigat-ot-turciia-varnenskite-kursanti-gotovi-za-dobrovolci-2217405 |accessdate=18 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 30 March, the Minister of Health Kiril Ananiev decreed wearing masks in public mandatory, both outdoors and indoors, despite nationwide protective equipment shortages and soaring prices.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.dw.com/bg/%D0%B2-%D1%81%D1%82%D0%B0%D1%80%D0%B0-%D0%B7%D0%B0%D0%B3%D0%BE%D1%80%D0%B0-%D1%88%D0%B8%D1%8F%D1%82-%D0%BF%D1%80%D0%B5%D0%B4%D0%BF%D0%B0%D0%B7%D0%BD%D0%B8-%D0%BC%D0%B0%D1%81%D0%BA%D0%B8-%D0%BD%D0%B0-%D0%B0%D0%BA%D0%BE%D1%80%D0%B4-%D0%BF%D0%BE-%D0%BC%D0%BE%D0%B4%D0%B5%D0%BB-%D0%BE%D1%82-%D1%81%D1%8A%D0%B2%D0%B5%D1%82%D1%81%D0%BA%D0%BE-%D0%B2%D1%80%D0%B5%D0%BC%D0%B5/a-52926981|title=\u0412 \u0421\u0442\u0430\u0440\u0430 \u0417\u0430\u0433\u043e\u0440\u0430 \u0448\u0438\u044f\u0442 \u043f\u0440\u0435\u0434\u043f\u0430\u0437\u043d\u0438 \u043c\u0430\u0441\u043a\u0438 \u043d\u0430 \u0430\u043a\u043e\u0440\u0434. \u041f\u043e \u043c\u043e\u0434\u0435\u043b \u043e\u0442 \u0441\u044a\u0432\u0435\u0442\u0441\u043a\u043e \u0432\u0440\u0435\u043c\u0435.|language=bg-BG|date=26 Mar 2020|website=www.dw.com|url-status=live|access-date=30 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.mediapool.bg/prokuraturata-zapochna-delo-za-spekula-zaradi-maski-ot-10-lv-news305261.html|title=\u041f\u0440\u043e\u043a\u0443\u0440\u0430\u0442\u0443\u0440\u0430\u0442\u0430 \u0437\u0430\u043f\u043e\u0447\u043d\u0430 \u0434\u0435\u043b\u043e \u0437\u0430 \u0441\u043f\u0435\u043a\u0443\u043b\u0430 \u0437\u0430\u0440\u0430\u0434\u0438 \u043c\u0430\u0441\u043a\u0438 \u043e\u0442 10 \u043b\u0432.|language=bg-BG|date=26 Mar 2020|website=mediapool.bg|url-status=live|access-date=30 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.mh.government.bg/bg/novini/aktualno/grazhdanite-koito-se-namirat-v-zakriti-ili-na-otkr/|title=\u0413\u0440\u0430\u0436\u0434\u0430\u043d\u0438\u0442\u0435, \u043a\u043e\u0438\u0442\u043e \u0441\u0435 \u043d\u0430\u043c\u0438\u0440\u0430\u0442 \u0432 \u0437\u0430\u043a\u0440\u0438\u0442\u0438 \u0438\u043b\u0438 \u043d\u0430 \u043e\u0442\u043a\u0440\u0438\u0442\u0438 \u043e\u0431\u0449\u0435\u0441\u0442\u0432\u0435\u043d\u0438 \u043c\u0435\u0441\u0442\u0430, \u0442\u0440\u044f\u0431\u0432\u0430 \u0434\u0430 \u043d\u043e\u0441\u044f\u0442 \u0437\u0430\u0449\u0438\u0442\u043d\u0430 \u043c\u0430\u0441\u043a\u0430|language=bg-BG|date=30 March 2020|website=|publisher=Ministry of Health|url-status=live|access-date=30 March 2020}}</ref> The policy seemed to contradict Ananiev's earlier statement from 9 March that producing the needed gear \"will take months\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.dnevnik.bg/bulgaria/2020/03/09/4038339_shte_sa_nujni_meseci_za_da_se_izrabotiat_nujnite_maski/|title=\u0429\u0435 \u0441\u0430 \u043d\u0443\u0436\u043d\u0438 \u043c\u0435\u0441\u0435\u0446\u0438, \u0437\u0430 \u0434\u0430 \u0441\u0435 \u0438\u0437\u0440\u0430\u0431\u043e\u0442\u044f\u0442 \u043d\u0435\u043e\u0431\u0445\u043e\u0434\u0438\u043c\u0438\u0442\u0435 \u043c\u0430\u0441\u043a\u0438 \u0438 \u0437\u0430\u0449\u0438\u0442\u043d\u0438 \u043e\u0431\u043b\u0435\u043a\u043b\u0430, \u043e\u0431\u044f\u0432\u0438 \u0410\u043d\u0430\u043d\u0438\u0435\u0432|language=bg-BG|date=9 Mar 2020|website=dnevnik.bg|url-status=live|access-date=30 March 2020}}</ref> As a misconduct falling under article 209a of the Health Law, passed on 13 March, which does not discriminate between offenses, failing to wear a mask is fined BGN 5,000 (EUR 2,555).<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.mediapool.bg/noseneto-na-maska-stava-zadalzhitelno-obnovena-news305456.html|title=\u041d\u043e\u0441\u0435\u043d\u0435\u0442\u043e \u043d\u0430 \u043c\u0430\u0441\u043a\u0430 \u0441\u0442\u0430\u0432\u0430 \u0437\u0430\u0434\u044a\u043b\u0436\u0438\u0442\u0435\u043b\u043d\u043e (\u043e\u0431\u043d\u043e\u0432\u0435\u043d\u0430)|last=|first=|date=30 Mar 2020|website=mediapool.bg|language=Bulgarian|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=30 Mar 2020}}</ref> In a major U-turn the minister rescinded the decree the following day, citing \"the lack of public consensus\" on the measure.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.dnevnik.bg/bulgaria/2020/03/31/4048340_koronavirusut_v_bulgariia_ananiev_otmeni_zapovedta_si/?ref=home_mainStory|title=\u041a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441\u044a\u0442 \u0432 \u0411\u044a\u043b\u0433\u0430\u0440\u0438\u044f: \u0410\u043d\u0430\u043d\u0438\u0435\u0432 \u043e\u0442\u043c\u0435\u043d\u0438 \u0437\u0430\u043f\u043e\u0432\u0435\u0434\u0442\u0430 \u0441\u0438 \u0437\u0430 \u0437\u0430\u0434\u044a\u043b\u0436\u0438\u0442\u0435\u043b\u043d\u0438\u0442\u0435 \u043c\u0430\u0441\u043a\u0438|last=|first=|date=31 Mar 2020|website=dnevnik.bg|language=Bulgarian|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=31 Mar 2020}}</ref>\n\n=== Testing ===\nAs of 24 March, there are 5 laboratories testing for COVID-19 in the country with a capacity of 300 tests per day. The total number of tests done by March 26 was 6,454, with 264 confirmed cases and a rate of infection around 4.1%.<ref>{{cite news |title= \u041c\u0435\u0434\u0438\u0446\u0438\u043d\u0441\u043a\u0438\u044f\u0442 \u0441\u044a\u0432\u0435\u0442 \u043f\u0440\u0435\u0434\u043b\u0430\u0433\u0430 \u043c\u0430\u0441\u043e\u0432 \u0441\u043a\u0440\u0438\u043d\u0438\u043d\u0433 \u0437\u0430 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441 |url=https://www.capital.bg/politika_i_ikonomika/covid/2020/03/24/4045342_medicinskiiat_suvet_predlaga_masov_skrining_za/ |accessdate=24 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n=== Medication ===\nAfter testing positive for COVID-19, business magnate [[Kiril Domuschiev]] announced that his company will procure [[chloroquine]] from foreign sources and donate it to the national coronavirus task force. Chloroquine, a [[quinine]] drug, has shown positive effects on COVID-19 patients in China and France. The Bulgarian government is looking into import opportunities from China and domestic production by local pharmaceutical companies.<ref>{{cite news |title=\u041c\u0435\u0434\u0438\u043a\u0430\u043c\u0435\u043d\u0442\u0438 \u0441\u0440\u0435\u0449\u0443 COVID-19: \u0429\u0435 \u043f\u043e\u043c\u043e\u0433\u043d\u0435 \u043b\u0438 \u0445\u043b\u043e\u0440\u043e\u0445\u0438\u043d\u044a\u0442 \u0438 \u0449\u0435 \u0433\u043e \u043f\u043e\u043b\u0437\u0432\u0430\u043c\u0435 \u043b\u0438 \u0443 \u043d\u0430\u0441 |url=https://dnes.dir.bg/na-fokus/novite-lekarstva-za-covid-19-shte-pomogne-li-hlorihinat-i-shte-go-polzvame-li-u-nas |accessdate=21 March 2020}}</ref> Exports of all quinine-based drugs were prohibited until further notice, and 35,000 doses of quinine-based [[Analgin]] for export have been diverted for domestic consumption. Another 250,000 doses of the drug can reportedly be produced on a short notice by local pharmaceutical companies.<ref>{{cite news |title=\u0411\u043e\u0440\u0438\u0441\u043e\u0432 \u0432\u044a\u0437\u043b\u043e\u0436\u0438 \u043d\u0430 \u0410\u043d\u0430\u043d\u0438\u0435\u0432 \u0434\u0430 \u043e\u0441\u0438\u0433\u0443\u0440\u0438 \u0445\u0438\u043d\u0438\u043d\u043e\u0432\u0438 \u043b\u0435\u043a\u0430\u0440\u0441\u0442\u0432\u0430 \u0437\u0430 \u0431\u044a\u043b\u0433\u0430\u0440\u0438\u0442\u0435 |url=https://segabg.com/hot/category-bulgaria/kiril-ananiev-zabrani-iznosa-na-hininovi-lekarstva |accessdate=21 March 2020}}</ref> On the 24th of March, Mr Domuschiev donated 100 packs of chloroquine containing 100 pills each. This will be enough for 320 critically ill patients. \n\n[[Bulgaria]]n biotechnology company Micar21 has been developing a general coronavirus vaccine in the past four years, and announced that it will begin clinical trials of a SARS-CoV-2 vaccine based on this research in mid-2020.<ref>{{cite news |title=\u041a\u043e\u0441\u0442\u0430\u0434\u0438\u043d \u041f\u0435\u0442\u043a\u043e\u0432, \u0421\u043e\u0444\u0438\u044f \u0422\u0435\u0445 \u041f\u0430\u0440\u043a: \u0420\u0430\u0431\u043e\u0442\u0438\u043c \u0441 \u0438\u043d\u043e\u0432\u0430\u0442\u0438\u0432\u043d\u0438 \u0444\u0438\u0440\u043c\u0438, \u043a\u043e\u0438\u0442\u043e \u0441\u0430 \u0440\u0430\u0437\u0440\u0430\u0431\u043e\u0442\u0438\u043b\u0438 \u043c\u043e\u043b\u0435\u043a\u0443\u043b\u0430 \u0437\u0430 \u043b\u0435\u0447\u0435\u043d\u0438\u0435 \u043d\u0430 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441 |url=http://focus-news.net/news/2020/03/10/2755591/kostadin-petkov-sofiya-teh-park-rabotim-s-inovativni-firmi-koito-sa-razrabotili-molekula-za-lechenie-na-koronavirus.html |accessdate=10 March 2020 |agency=Focus |date=10 March 2020}}</ref> The company announced that with government support in funding and shorter clinical trial protocols, the drug could be synthesised in two months.<ref>{{cite news |title=\u0425\u0438\u043c\u0438\u043a\u044a\u0442 \u0424\u0438\u043b\u0438\u043f \u0424\u0440\u0430\u0442\u0435\u0432: \u0414\u043e 2 \u043c\u0435\u0441\u0435\u0446\u0430 \u043c\u043e\u0436\u0435\u043c \u0434\u0430 \u0438\u043c\u0430\u043c\u0435 \u043b\u0435\u043a\u0430\u0440\u0441\u0442\u0432\u043e \u0441\u0440\u0435\u0449\u0443 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441\u0430 |url=https://www.168chasa.bg/Article/8297522?fbclid=IwAR1el8pNxVpsZsbzZjE-LrDGO3XfZYaD4VdREstWaeX5yEGkasKHZlg-lmo |accessdate=18 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n=== Criticism ===\nGeorgi Todorov, a Bulgarian doctor with experience in viral breakouts in [[Ghana]], criticised the handling of the COVID-19 threat. In particular, Todorov stated that Bulgaria's health administration is so rife with [[nepotism]] that it cannot come up with any coherent response; as a result, infectious disease specialists were not taken into account when formulating response policies, and no specific locations were designated for potential COVID-19 cases. Todorov further assumed that infected individuals may have not been identified because of improper application of testing procedures.<ref>{{cite news |title=\u0411\u044a\u0440\u043a\u0430\u0442 \u0441 \u0442\u0435\u0441\u0442\u043e\u0432\u0435\u0442\u0435 \u0437\u0430 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441 \u0443 \u043d\u0430\u0441, \u0437\u0430\u0442\u043e\u0432\u0430 \u043d\u0435 \u043e\u0442\u043a\u0440\u0438\u0432\u0430\u0442 |url=https://e-vestnik.bg/31900/barkat-s-testovete-za-koronavirus-u-nas-zatova-ne-otkrivat/?fbclid=IwAR2_fhX6HCxpaKAQ0m9dXidrJu8E1pmJRyauCyXW0XPA3wKb1viuUqxOy6Q |accessdate=11 March 2020 |date=4 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nAccording to Prof. Milan Milanov, former manager of Pirogov Hospital, the government's response was \"catastrophically delayed\", although he added that there's no room for panic as COVID-19 treatment was \"the same as with influenza\".<ref>{{cite news |title=\u041f\u0440\u043e\u0444. \u041c\u0438\u043b\u0430\u043d \u041c\u0438\u043b\u0430\u043d\u043e\u0432: \u041e\u0447\u0430\u043a\u0432\u0430\u043c \u0432\u0437\u0440\u0438\u0432 \u043e\u0442 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441 \u0432 \u0421\u043e\u0444\u0438\u044f |url=https://www.24chasa.bg/novini/article/8286282 |accessdate=11 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n{{2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic}}\n\n[[Category:2020 coronavirus pandemic in Europe|Bulgaria]]\n[[Category:2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic by country and territory|Bulgaria]]\n[[Category:2020 in Bulgaria|coronavirus pandemic]]\n[[Category:Health in Bulgaria]]\n[[Category:Medical outbreaks in Bulgaria]]\n", "name_user": "Skycycle", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2020_coronavirus_pandemic_in_Bulgaria"}
{"title_page": "El Mirage, Arizona", "text_new": "{{short description|City in Arizona, United States}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=August 2017}}\n{{Infobox settlement\n|official_name            = El Mirage\n|settlement_type          = [[City]]\n|image_skyline            = El Mirage-2.JPG\n|imagesize                = 200px\n|image_caption            = Entrance to the town of '''El Mirage'''.\n|image_seal               = El Mirage AZ seal.png\n|image_map                = Maricopa County Arizona Incorporated and Unincorporated areas El Mirage Highlighted 0422220.svg\n|mapsize                  = 250px\n|map_caption              = Location of El Mirage in Maricopa County, Arizona.\n|image_map1               = \n|mapsize1                 = \n|map_caption1             = \n|pushpin_map              = USA\n|pushpin_map_caption      = Location in the United States\n|subdivision_type         = [[List of sovereign states|Country]]\n|subdivision_type1        = [[U.S. state|State]]\n|subdivision_type2        = [[List of counties in Arizona|County]]\n|subdivision_name         = [[United States]]\n|subdivision_name1        = [[Arizona]]\n|subdivision_name2        = [[Maricopa County, Arizona|Maricopa]]\n|government_type          = \n|leader_title             = [[Council\u2013manager government|Council/Manager]]\n|leader_name              = Alexis Hermosillo\n|established_date         = 1951\n|area_magnitude           = \n|area_total_km2           = 25.78\n|area_total_sq_mi         = 9.95\n|area_land_km2            = 25.63\n|area_land_sq_mi          = 9.89\n|area_water_km2           = 0.15\n|area_water_sq_mi         = 0.06\n|elevation_ft             = 1145\n|elevation_m              = 349\n|population_as_of         = [[2010 United States Census|2010]]\n|population_est           = 35670\n|pop_est_as_of            = 2018\n|pop_est_footnotes        = <ref name=\"USCensusEst2018\"/>\n|population_footnotes     = <ref name =\"FactFinder\">{{cite web|title=American FactFinder|url=http://factfinder2.census.gov/faces/nav/jsf/pages/index.xhtml|publisher=[[United States Census Bureau]]|accessdate=June 18, 2014}}</ref>\n|population_total         = 31797\n|population_metro         = \n|population_density_km2   = 1391.83\n|population_density_sq_mi = 3604.85\n|timezone                 = [[Mountain Standard Time Zone|MST]] (no [[Daylight savings time|DST]])\n|utc_offset               = -7\n|coordinates              = {{coord|33|36|32|N|112|19|29|W|region:US_type:city|display=inline,title}}\n|timezone_DST             = \n|utc_offset_DST           = \n|postal_code_type         = [[ZIP code]]\n|postal_code              = 85335\n|area_code                = [[Area code 623|623]]\n|blank_name               = [[Federal Information Processing Standard|FIPS code]]\n|blank_info               = 04-22220\n|blank1_name              = [[Geographic Names Information System|GNIS]] feature ID\n|blank1_info              = {{GNIS 4|24845}}\n|website                  = [http://www.cityofelmirage.org/ cityofelmirage.org]\n|footnotes                = \n|unit_pref = Imperial\n|area_footnotes = <ref name=\"CenPopGazetteer2016\">{{cite web|title=2018 U.S. Gazetteer Files|url=https://www2.census.gov/geo/docs/maps-data/data/gazetteer/2018_Gazetteer/2018_gaz_place_04.txt|publisher=United States Census Bureau|accessdate=Jul 1, 2019}}</ref>\n}}\n\n'''El Mirage''' is a city in [[Maricopa County, Arizona|Maricopa County]], [[Arizona]], [[United States]]. According to the U.S. Census estimates in 2018, the population of the city is 35,670.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://factfinder.census.gov/faces/tableservices/jsf/pages/productview.xhtml?src=CF |title=Archived copy |access-date=January 31, 2019 |archive-url=https://wayback.archive-it.org/all/20170524215206/https://factfinder.census.gov/faces/tableservices/jsf/pages/productview.xhtml?src=CF |archive-date=May 24, 2017 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n\n==Geography==\nEl Mirage is located at {{coord|33|36|32|N|112|19|29|W|type:city}} (33.608988, -112.324654).<ref name=\"GR1\">{{cite web|url=https://www.census.gov/geo/www/gazetteer/gazette.html|publisher=[[United States Census Bureau]]|accessdate=April 23, 2011|date=February 12, 2011|title=US Gazetteer files: 2010, 2000, and 1990}}</ref>\n\nAccording to the [[United States Census Bureau]], the city has a total area of {{convert|9.7|sqmi|km2}}, all of it land.\n\n==Demographics==\n{{US Census population\n|1960= 1723\n|1970= 3258\n|1980= 4307\n|1990= 5001\n|2000= 7609\n|2010= 31797\n|estyear=2018\n|estimate=35670\n|estref=<ref name=\"USCensusEst2018\">{{cite web|url=https://www.census.gov/programs-surveys/popest/data/tables.2018.html|title=Population and Housing Unit Estimates|accessdate=June 4, 2019}}</ref>\n|align-fn=center\n|footnote=U.S. Decennial Census<ref name=\"DecennialCensus\">{{cite web|url=https://www.census.gov/prod/www/decennial.html|title=Census of Population and Housing|publisher=Census.gov|accessdate=June 4, 2016|archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/6YSasqtfX?url=http://www.census.gov/prod/www/decennial.html|archive-date=May 12, 2015|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n}}\n\nAs of the [[census]] of 2000, there were 7,609 people, 2,121 households, and 1,737 families residing in the city. The [[population density]] was 786.8 people per square mile (303.8/km\u00b2). There were 3,162 housing units at an average density of 326.9 per square mile (126.3/km\u00b2). The racial makeup of the city was 66.26% [[Race (United States Census)|White]], 3.29% [[Race (United States Census)|Black]] or [[Race (United States Census)|African American]], 0.85% [[Race (United States Census)|Native American]], 0.38% [[Race (United States Census)|Asian]], 0.05% [[Race (United States Census)|Pacific Islander]], 26.18% from [[Race (United States Census)|other races]], and 2.98% from two or more races. 66.82% of the population were [[Race (United States Census)|Hispanic]] or [[Race (United States Census)|Latino]] of any race.\n\nThere were 2,121 households out of which 48.8% had children under the age of 18 living with them, 55.3% were [[Marriage|married couples]] living together, 17.7% had a female householder with no husband present, and 18.1% were non-families. 13.0% of all households were made up of individuals and 3.7% had someone living alone who was 65 years of age or older. The average household size was 3.59 and the average family size was 3.87.\n\nIn the city, the population was spread out with 36.8% under the age of 18, 14.1% from 18 to 24, 28.6% from 25 to 44, 13.8% from 45 to 64, and 6.6% who were 65 years of age or older. The median age was 25 years. For every 100 females, there were 105.5 males. For every 100 females age 18 and over, there were 105.0 males.\n\nThe median income for a household in the city was $33,813, and the median income for a family was $33,468. Males had a median income of $25,176 versus $19,192 for females. The [[per capita income]] for the city was $10,342. About 12.6% of families and 15.9% of the population were below the [[poverty line]], including 14.2% of those under age 18 and 22.0% of those age 65 or over.\n\nEl Mirage is near Luke U.S. Air Force Base, the largest Fighter Pilot Training Base in the North Atlantic Treaty Organization (NATO), and can boast that it has the highest paid city manager per capita in the Phoenix, Arizona metropolitan area\n{{clear}}\n\n==Historic structures of El Mirage==\n{{Gallery\n|title=Historic structures<br>[[File: El Mirage-1.JPG|center|250px|thumb|Front of the former city hall building.]]\n|width=180px\n|height=200px\n|align=center\n|lines=4\n|File:El Mirage-Agua Fria River Bridge- 1895-2.JPG|Historic El Mirage '''Agua Fria River Bridge''' built in 1895.\n|File:El Mirage-Agua Fria River Bridge- 1895-1.JPG|Different view of the historic '''\"Agua Fria River Bridge\u201d'''.  \t \n|File: El Mirage-El Mirage Motel-1937-1.JPG |Different view of the office of '''El Mirage Motel'''. \n|File: El Mirage-El Mirage Motel-1937-7.JPG  |The rooms of '''El Mirage Motel''', such as this one, are in a state of total abandonment.  \n|File: El Mirage-El Mirage Motel-1937-6.JPG |Different view of the individual rooms of '''El Mirage Motel'''. \n|File: Former El Mirage-City Hall-2.jpg |'''Former El Mirage City Hall''' located at 12145 NW Grand Ave.\n|File: El Mirage-El Mirage Motel-1937-5.JPG | '''El Mirage Motel'''. These are the individual rooms of the motel which were used by motorist who traveled through Grand Ave. \n|File: El Mirage-El Mirage Motel-1937-2.JPG |'''El Mirage Motel''' was built out of fieldstone in 1937 and is located at 12229 NW Grand Ave. This is the office of the motel which was used by motorist who traveled through Grand Ave. The property is in state of abandonment.\n}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n*https://web.archive.org/web/20100415023621/http://peopleofelmirage.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/04/City-Manager-Salary.pdf Surprise Time Newspaper-City Managers Salary\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.cityofelmirage.org/ Official Website]\n\n{{Maricopa County, Arizona}}\n{{Phoenix Metropolitan Area}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Cities in Arizona]]\n[[Category:Cities in Maricopa County, Arizona]]\n[[Category:Phoenix metropolitan area]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|City in Arizona, United States}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=August 2017}}\n{{Infobox settlement\n|official_name            = El Mirage\n|settlement_type          = [[City]]\n|image_skyline            = El Mirage-2.JPG\n|imagesize                = 200px\n|image_caption            = Entrance to the town of '''El Mirage'''.\n|image_seal               = El Mirage AZ seal.png\n|image_map                = Maricopa County Arizona Incorporated and Unincorporated areas El Mirage Highlighted 0422220.svg\n|mapsize                  = 250px\n|map_caption              = Location of El Mirage in Maricopa County, Arizona.\n|image_map1               = \n|mapsize1                 = \n|map_caption1             = \n|pushpin_map              = USA\n|pushpin_map_caption      = Locati